        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 1 at 7:28PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Erie, or 23 miles north of Denver, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Hail may
accumulate on roadways causing hazardous travel.

Locations impacted include...
Thornton, Broomfield, Brighton, Lafayette, Erie, Firestone,
Frederick, Fort Lupton, Dacono, Todd Creek and Wattenburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
